records.addlTxt:
Defendant DeAngelo L Campbell in court, in custody, with attorney Joseph Edward Schubert.   Susan L. Opper appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court addresses the defendant's letter and his wish to move forward today.  Defendant wishes to continue with his plea and sentencing.  State makes recommendations.  Victim's Sisters makes statements.  Victim's Step mother makes statements. Victim's Father makes statements. Attorney Schubert makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  Court makes statements. 

The Court Orders the Following:  Count #2. 
Sentence of:
8 Years Imprisonment (Credit - 498 days)
4 Years of Initial Confinement
4 Years of Extended Supervision
Conditions of Extended Supervision:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
No contact with Victims family.
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of illegal controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Disclose to any physician in writing your drug history/dependency signed by your physician and provide a copy to your Agent. 
Sign All Releases for Agent;
Restitution: $2,000.00 to be paid to Victims family as a condition of extended supervision
COSTS:  $268.00  to be paid as a condition of extended supervision
Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
